fragments.plaintext: The difference between muting, restricting and blocking on Threads 👇

caption.text: The difference between muting, restricting and blocking on Threads 👇

fragments.plaintext: 🤫 Mute someone: When you mute someone you follow, you won’t see their threads or replies in your feed or receive alerts about their DMs. We won’t let them know you muted them — and you’ll still be following them.

caption.text: 🤫 Mute someone: When you mute someone you follow, you won’t see their threads or replies in your feed or receive alerts about their DMs. We won’t let them know you muted them — and you’ll still be following them.

fragments.plaintext: 🙅 Restrict someone: You won’t receive new notifications if they reply to you. You can restrict anyone on Threads, even if you don’t follow them. We won’t let them know — and you’ll still be following their profile.

caption.text: 🙅 Restrict someone: You won’t receive new notifications if they reply to you. You can restrict anyone on Threads, even if you don’t follow them. We won’t let them know — and you’ll still be following their profile.

fragments.plaintext: ❌ Block someone: They won’t be able to message you or see anything you post on Threads. People aren't notified when you block them.

caption.text: ❌ Block someone: They won’t be able to message you or see anything you post on Threads. People aren't notified when you block them.
